instead, I can use socket.io through the background script and then
communicate between the content script and my background script

CAMERA POSE ESTIMATION WORKS!!! (at least for these tests). best 40

The image shrinking made a huge difference.
Also because smaller images, less features, so reduced best matches N
   to 40

perhaps the images are too high resolution. Shrunk them by ~1/4

I believe that feature matching works based on locality, each feature
point has a certain "size" (eg 10px radius)
I forgot where I read this.

So perhaps the image is so high resolution, that the feature size is
very small relatively, and so it's capturing small details that have too
many matches. If I decrease the image size, the feature radius captures
more of the image, and each feature becomes more unique (I think)
